@NODE noindex "How to make CD Configs for CDs without index files!"
@{u}Making CD Configs for CDs without index files!@{uu}

@{b}DirScanner@{ub}, available when you register LSD Doors, can automate this
procedure for you and make index files & indexes for CDs without index files!
No more manual labour! @{" Register today! " LINK registration} :)

This is a sneaky idea I had and it seems to work :)...
I think it is easier to show this in steps.... So lets go...! 

1. Create a directory in Doors:KewlCD/Index/ with an appropriate name for the 
   CD, i.e. GIF's Galore might be Doors:KewlCD/Index/GIFSGAL/ ..

2. Check out the "list" command that comes with Workbench, as these CDs do not
   have comments with the files we shall use the date of the file as the
   comment (well, its better than nothing!).
   
3. Do a full "list" of all directories on the CD, and redirect the output
   to the Doors:KewlCD/Index/{nameofdir}/ - replacing {nameofdir} with the name
   of the directory you created for this CD. If you don't know how to do this
   an example might be...
   
   @{b}List CD0:Pictures/GIFs >Doors:KewlCD/Index/GIFSGAL/GIFS.txt NOHEAD@{ub}
   
   Do it for every directory on the CD... Now time to make the CD Config ...
   
4. Refer to the section on @{"Making a CD Config" LINK "cd.cfg"} but when
   entering the index file, refer to the one you created in 
   Doors:KewlCD/Index/{nameofdir}/ of course. Also when creating lines 4 & 5
   you will have to consider the following recommendations:
   
   > The filename field can change size if huge filenames are in it, so you may
     hafta re-do the list without the file in it as otherwise it would cause
     problems. The standard I think is 24 characters for this field, so use
     this value if possible.
     
   > The filesize field is a right-justified field, KewlCDPro should cope (not
     tested) but assume the biggest file will be 9999k in size.
     
   > The comment field can be the filedate, as I can't think what else you 
     can put in the comment field.
   
   > If you forget the NOHEAD argument when using list, the header size must be
     set to 1 because of the bit list puts on the top.
   
5. If you don't know what i'm on about or i've lost you, you're obviously not
   that knowledgeable of the Amiga or life so please don't attempt this and
   seriously think about shutting your BBS down (alternativley you can ask
   someone to do it for you :)..)

Thats all for now! More handy hints from me some other time, maybe, after I
have discovered what the BED does.

@ENDNODE


@NODE History "History!"
@{u}History@{uu}
 
Names within < > indicate they reported the bug/suggested the feature.

V2.1 - Got it all together for a full release! I think I got all the bugs
       sorted including the support programs. Have fun :).

V2.0 - KewlCDPro has now gone shareware, there arn't actually any major
       functions disabled or anything, but you cannot use the new configuration
       editor plus there are annoying nag requesters. Sorta, you can use it
       fine just hopefully guilt trippy for everybody :o).

       Requires the LSD Doors or *NEW* Other-registration keyfile for full use,
       see @{" registration " LINK registration} for more information.
       
       Included configuration editor (requires either one of those Keyfiles),
       use this to configure & update KewlCDPro!
       
       Added some items to the configuration, if you can use the configuration
       editor simply select @{b}Import > KewlCDPro 1.6@{ub} from the menu and
       save to update, otherwise see the @{" Configuration section " LINK conf}.
       
       Added pre-fetch copy to the buffered download system, in English this
       means the next file to be download will be copied as the current one is
       downloading <Sykoe>.
       
       Added "Request CD" option on the menu, at the moment this just writes a
       mail to the sysop, but its there for those shy users :o) <Julian Court>.
       
       Download window in MAXs now shows what CD the file is coming from (e.g.
       AMINET20_1: - an assign), useful for CD stackers <Sykoe>.
       
       Added < > , . and [ ] for section navigation Next/Previous.
       
       Changed *A LOT* of cosmetics, I think it looks a lot more professional
       now, some of these changes suggested by Marty, others I just thought
       looked nice :o). You can also now configure the location of the CD NAME.
       
       Added nicer help screen!
       
       If theres a problem locating a file or something, KewlCD will now open a
       CON window on MAXs/Workbench telling you what went wrong.
       
       You can now download all marked files on other CDs at start-up if
       possible.
       
       Added @{b}Keyboard.cfg@{ub}, just like in MagicFile, now can configure
       all keys :o), see @{" here " LINK keyboard} for more info.
       
       Added two column mode for Mode 2 to fit twice as many CDs on the screen.
       Also improved mode 2, CDs that arn't available are now in RED, otherwise
       in yellow, and CDs beyond your access are simply not displayed. Mode 2
       is now for registered users only :P.
       
       File_IDs are now supported in searches (this took a LOT of playing).
       
       Added support for FLE, it's only basic for now but at least it's there,
       :) enable the "Use FLE" line in the @{" Configuration " LINK conf}.
       
       I joined NSA Design!

   * - Released a BETA version.
     
       Made a few graphical changes, added a few clear screens in, made the
       "You have marked files on other CDs" bit alot nicer!
       
       Fixed problems when it couldn't locate a file (msg reported was too
       long to fit on the screen!).
       
       Fixed a few problems with the config loader & debug bits.
       
       Big bug on downloading from the "marked files on other CDs" bit, it
       didn't actually work.
       
       Attempted a work-around for FLE trashing bug, slowly adding more FLE
       features in like to ratio bits.. More to come though! (yeh, right ;).)

       Pre-fetch cache copier now uses @{b}Runback@{ub} (included) to make the
       execution a bit neater (and hopefully work, too!).
       
       Re-wrote all path stripping code, it will now work if there are marked
       files off the root directory of a CD.
       
   * - Released a BETA version (#2).
   
       Added @{b}SectionSelectHeader.text@{ub} to display a header for the section
       selector screen.
       
       Added some extra error checking on start-up, will give more useful
       error messages :o).
       
       Added more debugging facilities, reports errors (and line numbers) on
       CD Configs. Also now has section number limit (about 600 sections).
       
       Increased buffers twofold, now can load upto 600 sections.
       
       Fixed a few display glitches with the section lister.
       
   * - Released a BETA version (#3).
   
       Removed FLE support (holding back development) it doesn't work, upgrade
       to "FB" if you insist on using a different filebase ;)
       
       Fixed mode 2 dual column displayer, now uses fixed positions <Sykoe>.
       
       Mode 2 now doesn't display the number for CDs that are out <Sykoe>.
       
       Adding archive-before-downloading for indexs & lists, see the section
       on @{" Compressed Downloads " LINK compress} for more info <Sykoe>.
       
       Added directory requester for local download, and stopped it from
       displaying all the ratio crap (what's the use, you're the sysop! ;)..)
       
       Added nice dotty load progress thingy (you'll see what I mean!)
       
       CPS is now calculated for all downloads instead of using the last
       file. This makes it better than the MagicFile BIG CPS routine.
       
       Byte ratio support from MagicFile added! Mother of god, huge f'ing
       piece of code I did for this. Anyway, now it looks really nice, the
       ratio-o-meter and BIG CPS support byte ratio :o), and so the following
       files have been added/updated: @{b}CPSAnsi.text@{ub}, @{b}CPSAnsiBF.text@{ub}, @{b}Ratio.text@{ub},
       @{b}RatioBF.text@{ub}.
       
   * - Released a BETA version (#4).
   
       Added archive lists switch.
       
       Free download code has been changed slightly, so it should report
       errors and stuff now better.
       
       Added a few more safety checks & fixed a coupla bugs.
       
       Local downloads are now for registered users only (well, I gotta make em
       register some how) ;)

   * - Released a BETA version (#5), although it was meant to be the full one!
              
V1.6 - Updated guide & files.

       Added BIG CPS screen after downloads from MagicFile. <Dr. X>
       Added ANSI's 'CPSANSI.text' and 'CPSFONT.text' for this feature., NOTE
       these are exactly the same as MagicFile's so you can use MagicFile
       BIGCPS ansi & font texts with KewlCDPro and vice versa!
       
       Centered the titles.
       
       Fixed a couple of bugs, free downloads now work :o).
       
       Updated a couple of bits of text & improved guide.
       
       Now requires MAX's Pro 1.54 (000) or MAX's Pro.
       
       Improved the buffer in both the main KewlCDPro and in KewlCD-Copy
       &Update, this should allow for larger .kewlcdpro (CD Config) files!

V1.5 - The last page feature now holds 30 pages instead of 1, if you find a CD
       with more than 30 pages-worth of files, please mail me! Another one,
       when you go to the top of the list and press up again, instead of doing
       nothing it will go to the last page (or beep if at first page).
       
       New config format to house several new features :-
       o The section name can now be anywhere on the screen.
       o The section number can be anywhere too.
       o The prompt is now on the menu instead of built into the program, 
         instead you can chose where you want the keypress cursor to be.
       o When downloading files from a local login, instead of bringing up a
         download window it'll copy files to a download directory on your hard
         disk so now even you, the sysop, can surf your CDs with ease!
         
       Slightly altered ANSI - if you are using the default one, copy over it
       with this one, if you are using your own, make sure the "KewlCD by Steve
       Clack" bit is now on the first line, first column. Also I updated the
       Help.text so copy that over too.
       
       The downloader didn't actually remove spaces from filenames if the 
       "copy to hard disk before downloading" feature was enabled (it removes
       spaces because of a bug in the MAXs downloader, if you have a CD-ROM
       with spaces in filenames, enable with function).
       
       For more info on the new config and more read the appropriate section of
       this guide, which has been updated in places. Oh and 'AmiScanner' is no 
       longer included, because I think everyones got it now and its available
       seperately on the Aminet.
       
       Killed two weird bugs, one was that the ghostly image of 'enter your
       phone number' was being displayed just before download and the other was
       that the last file in the marked files list might not always be unmarked
       after download, fixed them both, but they were weird??
       
       Dots are back in filesizes now because otherwise you get '14m' instead
       of '1.4m' on Aminet CDs.
       
       KewlCDPro is now @{" giftware " LINK BBS}, please register.
       
       Added nice centering thing to the intro (not on the menu mode), I think
       it looks quite nice though I was having some problems with the cursor
       positioning so 'not allowed to access' CDs are represented by a red dash
       for now until I figure out a way of making them totally invisible.
 
V1.4 - Now internally converts filenames to lowercase so that the marked
       files editor won't get shitty if there are capital letters.
       
       Fixed volume & directory "spaces" bug <Sykoe>.
       
       Added File_ID.diz support to File_ID embedded listings <Sykoe>!!!! This
       little fucker made me stop working on KewlCD for 3 months because of a
       silly typing error which I couldn't figure out :(, but anyway, its done!
       
       Fixed bug when downloading results of "view-only" file listings.  
       .       
       Fixed version strings within executables.
       .
       Changed some of the operations & text, also the keypad does not change
       (all features of it work in mark mode or not) so that means yes I have
       put TOP & BOTTOM when you arn't in the marking session as well ;).
       
       Now works on multinode systems although the executable is huge now!
       
       Added a lot of error trapping so it should not quit totally if an
       error occours, BUT, if your CD is scratched up, its possible that
       your entire BBS will lock up cos the reader might get stuck :/.
       
       Updated KewlCDCopy + Update into one prog, KewlCD-Copy&Update -
       select which function you want at the start, also this prog has many
       enhancements over the old version.

V1.3 - Fixed major bug which meant the last CD in the Kewlcd.cfg was
       ignored (or KewlCD failed), dont know how this one slipped through.
       Removed WORDWRAP from guide, some people still use topaz/8 as
       system default font <smirk> and so the wordwrap messed up stuff,
       especially in this section <Niki Murkett>.
       Added some marked files management, tells users if they have marked
       files on other CDs when they enter the door and gives them several
       options on what to do with them <Sykoe>.
       Added "Copy to HD" feature <Niki Murkett/Sykoe>.
       Updated Kewlcd.cfg because of above, header changed too.
       Re-worked and added to this guide a bit.

V1.2 - Converted sourcecode to "Kewl Doors" (by Niki Murkett) instead of
       the old Ari Tsironis extension. Fixed a couple of bugs I noticed
       while I was doing this too and improved some code.
       Added free downloads for index files etc, the user will be given
       back any time and download ratio spent on the file after the
       download, this should work OK but in the worst case a user won't
       be given back downloads/time (if he/she hangs up too soon).
       Improved a couple of routines I spotted and added more error
       checking in.
       Fixed bug in "Clear all Marked Files" <Ozz Scott>.
       Removed 'mode 0' because if you *really* need it you just put in
       'mode 1' instead and take out all CDs in the KewlCD.cfg except one.
       The intro/menu system is now totally automatic and the prompt on
       'mode 2' can now handle upto 99 CDs <Sykoe>.
       Removed KewlCD.Intro because of the above.
       Added access levels for each CD <Richard Neville>.
       Format of KewlCD.cfg changed because of above.
       Changed listing method, some people seem to prefer it where the
       marker system only activates after people press an initial up, I
       see your point guys and this is standard <Niki Murkett, etc>.
       Fixed some bad English and documentation.
       Added what CD they are on to the main screen <Sykoe>.
       Changed Help.text to reflect new lister.
       Fixed "Page Up" bug with CDs with headers (hopefully) <Sykoe>.
       
V1.1 - Some of the code was duplicated 3 times (!) I have optimised the
       code, it is now also a little bit faster.
       Changed the "help.text" and the guide a little.
       Altered some of the operation and changed some small text.
       New bug-fixed version of AmiScanner (v1.9 - 2).
       Added tests into the search/listing routines so it will tell you
       exactly what file it can't find if there is an error in a CD config.
       Added RATIO screen to download, take a look - its quite nice :).
       Added new ANSI file to go with the ratio feature. Editable.
       Added version string into executable, go on, try 'Version KewlCDPro'
       in a shell (not forgetting the full path to KewlCDPro)!!
       Added some more CD Configs (hopefully Aminet 13 will be included!).
              
V1.0 - Removed custom file format and the conversion is now REAL TIME as
       the listings commence, it seems to be slightly faster than the old
       way too and saves a lot of farting around (ie. no more converter!)
       KewlCDCopy included for users of slow CD-ROMs.
       KewlCDUpdate to check older CD Config files for use with KewlCDPro.
       Fixed some text and added a visual section progress to the search
       routines.
       Added AmiScanner to the distribution archive.
       Trying to sort my brain out and stop fooling people with crap 
       programming, sorry for the hassle guys.
       CD Configs ending in ".kewlcdpro" for the new config format.
       
@ENDNODE

